+# ARIEC61850 integration audit for ArIED 61850 Tester 1.4.0
+
+This document records the source-level findings and corrections made after auditing the complete ARIEC61850 engine used by ArIED.
+
+## Critical findings
+
+### 1. Live IED identity was truncated at the first digit
+
+The previous live-model identity fallback treated the leading alphabetic characters of the first MMS Logical Device domain as the IED name. This produced incorrect identities for product and station names containing digits, for example:
+
+```text
+OLSF501ADD, OLSF501CB1, OLSF501Ln1_... -> OLSF
+```
+
+The engine now resolves identity from the full set of MMS Logical Device domains. Stable common domain stems and known LD role boundaries are evaluated without discarding product digits.
+
+Expected examples:
+
+```text
+OLSF501ADD + OLSF501CB1 + OLSF501Ln1_... -> IEDName OLSF501
+OCR7SR12CTRL                              -> IEDName OCR7SR, LDInst 12CTRL
+```
+
+Important limitation: MMS online discovery does not guarantee that the SCL `IED@name` is directly exposed by every server. A multi-domain common stem is therefore high-confidence evidence, while a single-domain split remains a heuristic unless an SCL/configured name is available.
+
+### 2. Multi-RCB report frames could be projected against the wrong DataSet
+
+All MMS InformationReport PDUs for one association enter one receive-router queue. Previously, each persistent monitor plan independently consumed the next queue item and immediately decoded it with that plan's `Members` list.
+
+With multiple active RCBs, this allowed the following unsafe sequence:
+
+```text
+report from RCB B
+    -> consumed while monitor A owns the receive slice
+    -> decoded with DataSet A members
+    -> wrong IEC object/value mapping
+```
+
+This can present as incorrect values, missing q/t companions, duplicate edges, or a live view that appears frozen.
+
+The corrected design is:
+
+```text
+one MMS InformationReport queue per association
+        -> decode report header first
+        -> identify RCB by exact RptID / RCB affinity / exact DataSet
+        -> map values with that monitor's actual DataSet members
+        -> enqueue the mapped frame to that monitor
+```
+
+Ambiguous reports are deliberately not projected against an arbitrary DataSet. The engine increments `UnroutedPersistentReportCount` and exposes a routing diagnostic instead.
+
+### 3. Quality decoder could mistake a two-bit Dbpos value for IEC quality
+
+The old recursive decoder accepted the first bit string it found. A two-bit double-point value could therefore be interpreted as IEC 61850 quality.
+
+Quality decoding now requires a bit-string payload capable of carrying the 13 quality bits. Short bit strings remain undecoded.
+
+### 4. q/t-only report frames were discarded
+
+When a report contained only a companion `q` or `t` member, the projector filtered it out because no process-value leaf was present in that frame.
+
+The projector now emits a partial companion update with explicit flags:
+
+```text
+HasValue     = false
+HasQuality   = true/false
+HasTimestamp = true/false
+```
+
+ArIED merges that update into the existing live point without replacing the process value or generating a false Sequence-of-Events value edge.
+
+## Report metadata now propagated
+
+ArIED receives report-frame metadata already decoded by ARIEC61850:
+
+- report-control reference;
+- RptID;
+- DataSet reference;
+- sequence number;
+- sub-sequence number;
+- segmentation continuation flag;
+- ConfRev;
+- buffer-overflow flag;
+- EntryID;
+- report time-of-entry;
+- local receive instant for internal ordering only.
+
+The runtime uses these fields for diagnostics and report-stream health. Local receive time is not shown as the IED process timestamp.
+
+## Runtime health checks added in ArIED
+
+- Refuses unsafe cross-RCB projection.
+- Reports the number of ambiguous/unrouted InformationReport frames.
+- Warns on BRCB buffer overflow.
+- Warns when ConfRev changes.
+- Detects non-contiguous report sequence numbers.
+- Retains the latest EntryID for later BRCB resume work.
+- Merges q/t-only updates without manufacturing a process-value event.
+
+## Source files changed
+
+### Engine
+
+- `Binding/Iec61850SmartValueReading.cs`
+- `Binding/Iec61850ValueBindingEngine.cs`
+- `Discovery/LiveIedModelDiscoveryBuilder.cs`
+- `Mms/MmsClientSession.cs`
+- `Mms/MmsPersistentReportMonitor.cs`
+- `Mms/MmsReportLiveSession.cs`
+- `Mms/MmsReportValueProjector.cs`
+- `Properties/AssemblyInfo.cs`
+
+### Tests
+
+- identity resolver tests;
+- quality bit-length guard test;
+- persistent multi-RCB routing tests;
+- report-header decoding test;
+- q-only report projection test.
+
+## Remaining live-validation items
+
+These require the target relay and a Windows .NET build environment:
+
+1. Confirm actual `RptID` values emitted by each vendor RCB.
+2. Exercise two or more RCBs concurrently and verify zero unsafe routing.
+3. Confirm q/t updates for separate DataSet members and structured Data Objects.
+4. Test segmented reports with real payloads.
+5. Validate sequence wrap behavior for the target vendor.
+6. Verify BRCB EntryID resume after disconnect/reconnect.
+7. Validate dynamic DataSet and URCB cleanup on stop/disconnect.
